What did you want to tell me?

473
00:21:24,762 --> 00:21:25,763
[Nicky clears throat]

474
00:21:25,847 --> 00:21:28,099
["Nocturne in E-Flat Major" by Chopin
playing softly]

475
00:21:28,182 --> 00:21:30,435
-[softly] I think I lost a cuff link.
-What did you say?

476
00:21:30,518 --> 00:21:32,645
[normal voice] I think
I lost a cuff link. I think…

477
00:21:32,729 --> 00:21:36,149
I looked down at my shirt and realized
that one of the cuff links had fallen off,

478
00:21:36,232 --> 00:21:39,110
and I realized
that I think it fell off into the coffin

479
00:21:39,193 --> 00:21:40,695
when I went to hug Nonna.

480
00:21:41,779 --> 00:21:45,533
What do you…
want me to do with that information?

481
00:21:45,616 --> 00:21:48,202
I don't-- I don't-- I don't know.
I'm just, I'm-- It was--

482
00:21:48,286 --> 00:21:51,164
-They were a gift from the church.
-Oh…

483
00:21:51,789 --> 00:21:55,335
-They're antique. So, I--
-Nicky, what are you talking about now?

484
00:21:56,252 --> 00:21:59,422
Nothing. I'm just saying… I don't know--
[whispers] I don't know what to do.

485
00:21:59,505 --> 00:22:00,381
[Natalie] Mm-hmm.

486
00:22:00,465 --> 00:22:01,966
I don't know. Get some new cuff links.

487
00:22:02,050 --> 00:22:03,551
Why are we talking about cuff links?

488
00:22:03,634 --> 00:22:07,263
Natalie, I don't recall inviting you
into this conversation. They're valuable.

489
00:22:07,347 --> 00:22:09,640
I believe they were gold.
It was a gold cuff link.

490
00:22:09,724 --> 00:22:14,020
It fell in, and I'm trying to figure out
if there's a way of getting them back.

491
00:22:14,103 --> 00:22:15,271
"Getting them back"? [scoffs]

492
00:22:15,355 --> 00:22:17,482
Honey, it's in the ground.
What are you gonna do?

493
00:22:17,565 --> 00:22:21,736
Well, I guess I don't…
I mean, I guess nothing. I guess nothing.

494
00:22:21,819 --> 00:22:23,821
I just thought,
since she was buried this morning,

495
00:22:23,905 --> 00:22:25,907
the soil might be loose enough to--

496
00:22:25,990 --> 00:22:27,950
-Nicholas!
-[Natalie] Oh my God.

497
00:22:28,034 --> 00:22:30,370
Are you suggesting
that we exhume my mother for a cuff link?

498
00:22:30,453 --> 00:22:34,123
No! Of course not. Of course not!

499
00:22:34,207 --> 00:22:35,416
["Nocturne" playing softly]

500
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:38,961
-Do they… do they do that?
-You have lost your mind officially.

501
00:22:39,045 --> 00:22:40,421
Natalie, I'm asking a question.

502
00:22:40,505 --> 00:22:42,673
Oh my God. That's my mother's naked back.

503
00:22:43,841 --> 00:22:45,301
-[Nicky] What?
-Mom. God…

504
00:22:45,385 --> 00:22:47,261
-Natalie, what did you press?
-Oh my God.

505
00:22:47,345 --> 00:22:49,514
These are the photos
in the memorial album.

506
00:22:49,597 --> 00:22:51,265
-Honey, fix it.
-Oh my God, no.

507
00:22:51,349 --> 00:22:52,934
You're the one holding the phone.

508
00:22:53,017 --> 00:22:54,685
-[woman] Honey, get it.
-Fuck. I'm so sorry.

509
00:22:54,769 --> 00:22:56,187
-[Nicky] Here.
-[muffled] Oh God.

510
00:22:56,270 --> 00:22:58,147
-[Natalie] Okay.
-[Nicky] I'm turning the TV off.

511
00:22:59,190 --> 00:23:04,362
Morgan was supposed to go through these,
and now she's nowhere to be found.

512
00:23:04,445 --> 00:23:07,073
My mother would be mortified.

513
00:23:07,156 --> 00:23:08,449
I understand. You know what?

514
00:23:08,533 --> 00:23:11,869
I think we could all benefit from being
a little bit kinder to one another.

515
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:13,079
-[woman] Mm…
-Okay?

516
00:23:13,162 --> 00:23:16,666
Everybody grieves in different ways.
And Morgan…

517
00:23:17,667 --> 00:23:20,420
Morgan is out there somewhere right now,

518
00:23:21,129 --> 00:23:22,797
knee-deep in grief.

519
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:24,882
-I'm sure she's at a rave.
-Now…

520
00:23:26,759 --> 00:23:28,845
Nonna can't be mortified, Ma.

521
00:23:29,554 --> 00:23:30,596
She's not here.

522
00:23:32,390 --> 00:23:33,474
She's in heaven.

523
00:23:34,058 --> 00:23:34,892
[gasps]

524
00:23:34,976 --> 00:23:36,227
Judging people there.

525
00:23:36,978 --> 00:23:38,271
Okay? [inhales]

526
00:23:38,354 --> 00:23:43,151
So I need you, for the first time
in your life, to just take a breath.

527
00:23:45,570 --> 00:23:48,156
Okay? This is a beautiful spread, Ma.

528
00:23:49,449 --> 00:23:52,118
You deserve to just sit down
and have a drink.

529
00:23:52,201 --> 00:23:54,954
-But we're about to start the slideshow.
-Yeah.

530
00:23:55,538 --> 00:23:57,248
After the slideshow then.

531
00:23:57,331 --> 00:23:58,166
Okay?

532
00:23:59,959 --> 00:24:02,253
Now, I think I have to go.

533
00:24:02,336 --> 00:24:04,213
-My head is hurting.
-[woman] Oh.

534
00:24:04,297 --> 00:24:05,465
And people are staring.

535
00:24:05,548 --> 00:24:07,633
All right, thank you.
I appreciate that, honey,

536
00:24:07,717 --> 00:24:09,844
because your face
is incredibly hard to look at.

537
00:24:09,927 --> 00:24:11,888
All right. So I'm going.

538
00:24:11,971 --> 00:24:13,014
-[woman] Okay.
-Okay?

539
00:24:13,097 --> 00:24:14,474
-I love you.
-[mouths] I love you.

540
00:24:14,557 --> 00:24:16,058
-Okay.
-Thank you.

541
00:24:21,189 --> 00:24:22,607
[Natalie sighs]

542
00:24:22,690 --> 00:24:23,774
[whispers] Are you okay?

543
00:24:24,609 --> 00:24:27,028
[whispers] Did you see
what Bethany was wearing?

544
00:24:27,111 --> 00:24:28,070
[whispers] I saw.

545
00:24:28,571 --> 00:24:29,906
[funky music playing]

546
00:24:29,989 --> 00:24:30,907
[grunts softly]

547
00:24:30,990 --> 00:24:32,992
[panting]

548
00:24:37,830 --> 00:24:38,748
[grunts]

549
00:24:55,139 --> 00:24:56,557
[gravel crunching]

550
00:25:03,314 --> 00:25:04,482
[music ends abruptly]

551
00:25:04,565 --> 00:25:05,483
[man] Hey.

552
00:25:05,566 --> 00:25:06,943
[music resumes]

553
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:13,282
[softly] God.

554
00:25:14,992 --> 00:25:15,993
[whispers] Morgan.

555
00:25:17,119 --> 00:25:17,995
Morgan.

556
00:25:18,079 --> 00:25:19,497
[music fades]

557
00:25:22,083 --> 00:25:23,000
Maria?

558
00:25:25,086 --> 00:25:28,548
I want to… thank you for coming.

559
00:25:29,173 --> 00:25:32,343
Um… I know that given what went down
between the two of you,

560
00:25:32,426 --> 00:25:34,845
that couldn't have been an easy decision.

561
00:25:34,929 --> 00:25:36,556
What are you talking about?

562
00:25:37,056 --> 00:25:39,016
Your mother was a bitch, but I loved her.

563
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:40,518
[inhales sharply] Mom always said,

564
00:25:40,601 --> 00:25:43,521
"Indifference is the worst thing
you can receive from a person."

565
00:25:43,604 --> 00:25:46,649
So, I-- Yeah, I don't really know much
about what happened…

566
00:25:46,732 --> 00:25:47,567
[inhales sharply]

567
00:25:47,650 --> 00:25:50,528
…but I think we could agree
that she could be critical. [chuckles]

568
00:25:50,611 --> 00:25:54,115
So you didn't write my mother
a thank-you card 15 years ago.

569
00:25:55,032 --> 00:25:59,078
She sent me a thank-you gift basket
for recommending my caterer.

570
00:25:59,161 --> 00:26:02,832
I'm supposed to send her a thank-you card
for the thank-you gift basket?

571
00:26:02,915 --> 00:26:04,458
-Well…
-I mean, it's insane, huh?

572
00:26:04,542 --> 00:26:06,752
I think that she heard
that you took it to church

573
00:26:06,836 --> 00:26:08,629
and you were handing it out to friends.

574
00:26:08,713 --> 00:26:14,051
Oh, so now she wants to control
what I do with the thank-you gift basket.

575
00:26:14,135 --> 00:26:17,013
I couldn't eat all that cheese by myself.

576
00:26:18,848 --> 00:26:19,890
Listen,

577
00:26:20,766 --> 00:26:22,935
for all your mother's shortcomings,

578
00:26:24,562 --> 00:26:26,272
you're a decent woman, Linda.

579
00:26:26,355 --> 00:26:31,360
You've built a very nice,
honorable family for yourself.

580
00:26:32,570 --> 00:26:34,196
Let's just agree, huh?

581
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:36,115
To let that be her legacy.

582
00:26:36,991 --> 00:26:38,159
Well, I…

583
00:26:38,659 --> 00:26:42,330
I appreciate that very much, Maria.
Thank you. [inhales]

584
00:26:45,291 --> 00:26:46,917
[both laughing]

585
00:26:49,337 --> 00:26:51,380
-I just want to remind you…
-Hm?

586
00:26:51,881 --> 00:26:54,925
…that I once lent her $18.

587
00:26:55,009 --> 00:26:57,136
-And I never got it back.
-You never got it back.

588
00:26:57,219 --> 00:26:58,554
-Yeah.
-I'm just saying.

589
00:26:58,638 --> 00:26:59,472
[Linda] Mm-hmm.

590
00:27:02,475 --> 00:27:03,601
[door opens, creaks]

591
00:27:03,684 --> 00:27:05,019
[softly] Wow.

592
00:27:05,102 --> 00:27:06,646
This is as far as you got?

593
00:27:06,729 --> 00:27:08,856
Okay, hey.
This is a lot harder than it looks, okay?

594
00:27:08,939 --> 00:27:10,650
I have blisters all over my hands.

595
00:27:10,733 --> 00:27:13,569
-You didn't use gloves?
-No, I didn't use gloves.

596
00:27:13,653 --> 00:27:17,156
I wasn't thinking about my hand health,
okay? I've never dug up a grave.

597
00:27:17,239 --> 00:27:20,493
I don't know what to do
in a situation like this.

598
00:27:20,576 --> 00:27:22,286
-Okay.
-[voice breaking] My back is fucked.

599
00:27:22,370 --> 00:27:24,121
My hands are fucked. [inhales deeply]

600
00:27:24,205 --> 00:27:26,374
We're fucked. And I fucking suck.

601
00:27:26,457 --> 00:27:28,042
-Yeah.
-Ow! [groans]

602
00:27:28,125 --> 00:27:29,001
Jesus.

603
00:27:29,085 --> 00:27:34,256
I'm gonna live my whole life having
never done anything that matters at all.

604
00:27:34,340 --> 00:27:36,050
Okay. All right.

605
00:27:36,133 --> 00:27:37,093
[insects chirping]

606
00:27:37,176 --> 00:27:39,762
Morgan, I'm gonna-- I'm gonna need you
to give me your hand.

607
00:27:40,262 --> 00:27:41,806
-Right now. Okay.
-Okay.

608
00:27:41,889 --> 00:27:42,973
Okay. Let's do it.

609
00:27:43,766 --> 00:27:45,309
-Okay.
-[grunting]

610
00:27:45,393 --> 00:27:48,437
-I need you… to pull it together.
-[Morgan pants]

611
00:27:48,521 --> 00:27:50,147
-Okay. Yes.
-All right?

612
00:27:50,231 --> 00:27:52,441
First of all, you're not a loser.

613
00:27:52,525 --> 00:27:54,568
You are a public school teacher.

614
00:27:54,652 --> 00:27:58,072
And aside from being a mother,
that is the most thankless job in America.

615
00:27:58,155 --> 00:28:00,366
Thank you.
I don't think I said I was a loser.

616
00:28:00,449 --> 00:28:02,493
-And if the two of us continue digging…
-Okay.

617
00:28:02,576 --> 00:28:05,162
…we should hit the casket
before the sun comes up.

618
00:28:05,246 --> 00:28:07,415
I never thought
I would ever say that out loud.

619
00:28:07,498 --> 00:28:08,999
Aw… You're gonna dig?

620
00:28:09,083 --> 00:28:10,334
[Morgan sobs softly]

621
00:28:10,418 --> 00:28:12,670
-I'm gonna dig.
-Aw… [exhales]

622
00:28:12,753 --> 00:28:14,714
Just, like, I've been here
all night, you know.

623
00:28:14,797 --> 00:28:15,631
Okay, okay.

624
00:28:15,715 --> 00:28:19,343
You showed up, you know? And somehow
you're doing the absolute bare minimum.

625
00:28:19,427 --> 00:28:21,762
-Okay.
-You know? It really-- It's kind of just…

626
00:28:21,846 --> 00:28:24,056
It's exactly what I needed right now,
you know?

627
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:24,974
Morgan.

628
00:28:25,057 --> 00:28:25,891
Yeah.

629
00:28:27,393 --> 00:28:28,811
Who is Alan Botkins?

630
00:28:29,395 --> 00:28:31,105
I don't know. Who is Alan Botkins?

631
00:28:31,188 --> 00:28:35,234
You tell me. You've been digging up
his grave for the past two hours.

632
00:28:35,317 --> 00:28:36,152
What?

633
00:28:37,653 --> 00:28:38,612
No, that's…

634
00:28:38,696 --> 00:28:41,532
-No, no. No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.
-Oh my…

635
00:28:41,615 --> 00:28:43,993
-No, that--
-Did you look at the headstone, Morgan?

636
00:28:44,076 --> 00:28:46,454
Or did you just see
a fresh plot and start digging?

637
00:28:46,537 --> 00:28:48,748
This is where the funeral took place.

638
00:28:50,875 --> 00:28:53,711
No, this is where the funeral took place.

639
00:28:55,463 --> 00:28:56,714
[gasps loudly]

640
00:28:56,797 --> 00:28:57,631
Morgan!

641
00:28:57,715 --> 00:29:00,593
No. No, no, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

642
00:29:00,676 --> 00:29:02,887
-What, what, what, what? It--
-Oh, man.

643
00:29:02,970 --> 00:29:03,971
[screams] God!

644
00:29:04,054 --> 00:29:05,890
It is fucking pitch out here.

645
00:29:05,973 --> 00:29:08,726
What are the odds
of two back-to-back fresh graves?

646
00:29:08,809 --> 00:29:12,271
We're in the new part
of the cemetery, so pretty likely.

647
00:29:12,772 --> 00:29:15,608
There's fresh graves
all over the place. There's--

648
00:29:15,691 --> 00:29:17,943
There's one right there. There's…

649
00:29:18,027 --> 00:29:21,030
-There's one over here. Fresh grave!
-No. No!

650
00:29:21,530 --> 00:29:22,615
There's two right here.

651
00:29:22,698 --> 00:29:25,034
I'm being dead serious.
I need you to be nice to me.

652
00:29:25,117 --> 00:29:27,328
Is this the current state
of the public education system?

653
00:29:27,411 --> 00:29:28,621
-Don't do that!
-Just saying…

654
00:29:28,704 --> 00:29:31,457
I knew it wasn't great,
but this is frightening.

655
00:29:31,540 --> 00:29:32,416
[Morgan mutters]

656
00:29:32,500 --> 00:29:35,377
Okay, okay, okay.
Stop it, I am dead serious.

657
00:29:36,670 --> 00:29:37,671
What the hell is this?

658
00:29:37,755 --> 00:29:39,048
It's a little shovel.

659
00:29:39,131 --> 00:29:41,383
No, this is a hoe, Morgan.

660
00:29:41,467 --> 00:29:42,593
This is a hoe.

661
00:29:42,676 --> 00:29:44,845
-What?
-What did you put in this bag?

662
00:29:44,929 --> 00:29:45,805
[yells] Shovels!

663
